  "response": "Python is a high-level, interpreted programming language known for its simplicity, readability, and versatility. Here are key details about Python:\n\n1. Key Characteristics:\n- Easy to learn and read\n- Open-source and free\n- Supports multiple programming paradigms\n- Dynamically typed language\n- Extensive standard library\n\n2. Key Features:\n- Clean and straightforward syntax\n- Automatic memory management\n- Object-oriented programming support\n- Large community and extensive libraries\n- Cross-platform compatibility\n\n3. Common Use Cases:\n- Web development\n- Data science and analysis\n- Machine learning and AI\n- Scientific computing\n- Automation and scripting\n- Game development\n- Desktop applications\n\n4. Popular Libraries and Frameworks:\n- Django (web development)\n- NumPy (scientific computing)\n- Pandas (data analysis)\n- TensorFlow (machine learning)\n- Pygame (game development)\n- Flask (web framework)\n\n5. Created By:\n- Guido van Rossum in 1991\n- Named after Monty Python comedy group\n\n6. Versions:\n- Python 2 (legacy)\n- Python 3 (current standard)\n\nPython is widely used in various industries and continues to grow in popularity due to its flexibility and ease of use.",
